description.text: We decided to make Spark more distinctive. We've changed her origins from being an average Everod-girl to ... well you'll see soon enough!
After settling for a basic body + pose we needed to find a good face for our new fighting girl.
We've landed on our favorite Spark body + face. Now to finish her outfit with some plants. But which ones?
I like your hat girl! Now to find the perfect color pallete for your outfit!

I think you've sparked a war! 
Uh ... well this is Spark! Look at her face we've changed it a little bit in the last few steps.
Now she is more than ready to thrash some Shields!
We've worked through the Fin prototypes and decided to start from scratch. Fin needed to be immediately recognizable, have a distinct shape and an outfit that fit his new job: Archeologist.
Aura went full out with design ideas for Fin, all of them fit him and maybe you'll see some of them in the future.
Fins design was really fun to think about. Look at these drills! It was either the big drill or the big tank. The choice was important to make Fins sprite distinctive!
We're getting real close here! These two certainly capture Fins spirit well. Let's combine them!
We've decided on a look now let's put in some color! Here we had to consider which colors weren't already represented by other characters in EndCycle VS.
Some more color Variations for the young Everodian!
Here we go! A distinct color, shape and personality for our ex-protagonist. We love him all the same though and whish him good luck whilst ice-fishing for artefacts!
Rozu's colors were pretty much a hole in one. We immediately fell in love with him.
Look at this precious boy and his glowing clothes. Wonder what's up with that....
We always knew we wanted the agents to be gender neutral, to have goggles...and keytars! Wh0 d0es that pers0n in the middle remind me 0f th0ugh?
At this point we only had to decide at a belt and pants-design. Notice the little batwing on their left shoulder. Makes them look regal.
It's fun to see which elements of these prototypes remain and which have left. The bat-wings now look like fish! What!
Bat-wing or no bat-wing? Our goal was to give them a fresh summer vibe so....

Here we go! A gender-neutral, goggle and keytar wearing design which we are really proud of! Similar to the punks these were designed as self-insert characters from the beginning and we hope you can identify with your Agent-avatars!

It's fun how Aura pretty much nailed this one right away. We wanted to give them more personality than the original "Crimson Grunt" designs! This design choice resulted in a completely new Crimson Force!
These versions of the Punks would've been really cool as well but we wanted their shape to be very different from the agents.
Look at racoon Punk over here!
You could imagine some Punks to look like this in their free time huh.

Here we had the basic design down and were figuring out how all players could play as a Punk-identity they felt comfortable with! We went with the option to add long/short haird and beard/no beard in any combination the player decided to have.
You come into a room and see all these Punks wyd.
5 reminds me of a certain pop-star. This design is from 2018...how visionary. Anyways it looks nothing like the Punks nowadays.
AV.Atar could be anywho or anyone! A suit of armor that hides the owners true identity!

A sleek suit stored inside a VOC. Anyone wearing this could ROCK your world MAN. 
Or pull a mighty number on ya. Anyone want Pizza?
When we got these designs we wanted to use them all. But one particular design stood out....
As you can see we've always been aiming for a friendly kind of weapon here.
Any of these would've been great really.
This would be so satisfying as a toy.
Mixing and matching these options was so fun. Imagine if a B4 kind of QT crawled up to you and started blasting. Fun!
B really came out of nowhere. And it stuck.
We've used Felix's design for a long time and even had a nice design for it in-game. But after a few years we've decided to make QT better fit in with the rest of the pixel-art.
This is a silly joke that has somehow persisted through all iterations of the game.
It's design was based on it's primarly function in the old EndCycle to teach players about de-buffs.
Always melting. Never resting. Is this pony reminding you of yourself? It should.
"Make an electric cat mixed with a tank" was the instruction. Honestly all 3 of these designs are winners.

We went with the cat we wanted to pet the most. 
Now let's decide on a cute color.

This design was a smooth process. 
We've got our cute electric cat! 
It is very popular among the offices of Azure Shield even if it causes an outage or two from time to time.
We wanted to have the Voxel Generators instantly recognizable like some kind of... buster.
Do you recognize who's back this is? We wanted the VXG to be a network consisting of the buster and a back piece. Nowadays every character has their own personal VXG.
#Orange_juice_and_toothpaste
Curvy and elegant this logo was rather unique wouldn't you say?

In concept art you keep narrowing down design choices until you land on the one everybody can agree on.
Any of these Sparks would've been good really but we went with 2A in the end.
3d was the second most popular choice in the team back then. But Azure Shield is already blue sooo....
We called this design "Ketchup and Mustard Spark". It's funny how her character remained the same through all iterations but her design nowadays is completely different isn't it.

Fin's jacket went through many iterations. We wanted to consider a style that looks cool, makes sense for the climate of Everod...
And would be easy to recreate for cosplayers! Now Fin looks completely different. Oh well.
Which of these designs is the most Anime? You heard me. The MOST Anime!
Blue shirt and red jacket huh.
We always knew that the AS grunts needed to look more futuristic than the CF ones.
Some neat color combinations here.
Some design choices here have made it into the actual agents design. This fella would actually fit into Azure Shield as an intern or something.
The one in the middle looks like proto-Spark. A coincidence I assure you.
A clash between two worlds! What goes better with coffee than some strawberry cheesecake?
